 {"id":"bd-32rw","title":"Fix flakey CLI test timeout for deprecated skills commands","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-02-06T16:46:04.470668197Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-06T16:51:55.467931042Z","closed_at":"2026-02-06T16:51:55.467905073Z","close_reason":"Raised CLI suite per-test timeout to match spawnJfp and prevent SIGTERM flakes","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":37,"issue_id":"bd-32rw","author":"QuietBasin","text":"Root cause: bun test default per-test timeout is 5000ms, but our CLI E2E helpers spawn bun run jfp.ts with 15-30s timeouts. Under parallel load, some spawn-based tests can exceed 5s and get SIGTERM (exit 143).\n\nFix: raise CLI suite timeout via test:cli/test:cli:coverage scripts (--timeout=30000) and add an explicit per-test timeout in packages/cli/__tests__/commands/skills.test.ts for extra robustness.","created_at":"2026-02-06T16:51:35Z"}]}
